1
00:00:02,080 --> 00:00:06,980
<i>I thought I had nothing left to lose.</i>

2
00:00:10,140 --> 00:00:11,880
<i>After so much pain,</i>

3
00:00:12,730 --> 00:00:15,730
<i>I wanted to believe that life...</i>

4
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:19,260
<i>would only bring happiness.</i>

5
00:00:23,350 --> 00:00:25,400
<i>Little by little, every day,</i>

6
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:30,520
<i>the things I once took for granted
are disappearing.</i>

7
00:00:33,350 --> 00:00:34,680
<i>But...</i>

8
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,990
I won't die...

9
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:43,360
until we see the fireworks together.

10
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:46,040
<i>I don't want to give up.</i>

11
00:00:48,475 --> 00:00:49,770
Koharu?

12
00:00:49,770 --> 00:00:50,970
Yes?

13
00:00:54,490 --> 00:00:55,980
Kakeru?

14
00:00:56,610 --> 00:00:57,610
Yeah.

15
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:01,220
How are you today?

16
00:01:02,095 --> 00:01:04,010
I'm doing fine.

17
00:01:04,010 --> 00:01:05,710
Good.

18
00:01:05,710 --> 00:01:07,975
Was it cold outside?

19
00:01:07,975 --> 00:01:09,315
Just a little.

20
00:01:09,980 --> 00:01:11,310
<i>I want to live...</i>

21
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:15,680
<i>and see the fireworks with Kakeru.</i>

22
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:03,090
[Episode 7]

23
00:02:04,005 --> 00:02:06,500
I'm so glad.

24
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,630
I heard you remember us now, Koharu.

25
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:11,480
Yuuko.

26
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:13,430
Sorry for worrying you.

27
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:16,580
Not at all. I'm just happy
you remember my name.

28
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:20,340
Koharu, guess who I am.

29
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:22,468
Hmm...

30
00:02:22,468 --> 00:02:23,710
Who might you be?

31
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:26,100
Come on, don't be like that!

32
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:28,060
<i>To Yuuko and Ushio,</i>

33
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:32,695
<i>I explained simply that
Koharu got her memories back.</i>

34
00:02:32,695 --> 00:02:33,935
Thank you.

35
00:02:40,465 --> 00:02:42,840
You're going to the fireworks, right?

36
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,850
Yeah.

37
00:02:44,610 --> 00:02:46,900
I'll be better by then.

38
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:51,400
I'll snag us the best spot bright and early.

39
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,966
Yuuko, we're meeting up at 4 a.m.

40
00:02:53,966 --> 00:02:56,321
What? That's still nighttime.

41
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:04,700
Sorry.

42
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:10,430
Why am I crying?

43
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,700
I'm just so excited for it.

44
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:19,740
If I can see the fireworks with everyone,

45
00:03:21,010 --> 00:03:22,360
I'd be...

46
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:25,220
so incredibly happy.

47
00:03:27,775 --> 00:03:29,720
- See you later.
- Later.

48
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,120
Yuuko?

49
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:44,430
Yeah. Sorry.

50
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,640
It's okay.

51
00:03:49,330 --> 00:03:51,110
Everything will be okay.

52
00:03:53,820 --> 00:03:54,940
Yeah.

53
00:04:04,205 --> 00:04:05,680
Visiting today?

54
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:08,285
Yeah. How about you?

55
00:04:08,285 --> 00:04:11,503
I'd go, but I'd just be in the way.

56
00:04:11,503 --> 00:04:12,918
Yeah, probably.

57
00:04:12,918 --> 00:04:14,088
Hey!

58
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,390
What's this?

59
00:04:18,210 --> 00:04:22,590
Ah, just a little something.

60
00:04:22,590 --> 00:04:24,620
Please don't push yourself.

61
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:31,650
Let's have some water.

62
00:04:32,990 --> 00:04:36,310
But I have to eat.

63
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:41,590
I promised I'd get better.

64
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:50,665
You've been coming here every day lately.

65
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:53,450
Oh, yes. I'm sorry.

66
00:04:53,450 --> 00:04:55,350
I appreciate it.

67
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:56,765
Huh?

68
00:04:56,765 --> 00:05:00,505
I'm sure your visits really cheer her up.

69
00:05:02,380 --> 00:05:03,380
Oh...

70
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:06,110
But...

71
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:11,740
Sometimes, I just don't know anymore.

72
00:05:13,605 --> 00:05:17,570
Whether what I'm doing is right or not.

73
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,550
Koharu...

74
00:05:22,210 --> 00:05:25,380
might not get better, even with effort.

75
00:05:28,850 --> 00:05:30,200
And yet...

76
00:05:32,620 --> 00:05:36,270
<i>I keep telling her to hang in there
and keep fighting.</i>

77
00:05:38,370 --> 00:05:41,520
I might be acting thoughtless.

78
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:54,060
I've seen many patients over the years.

79
00:05:55,155 --> 00:06:00,110
Among them were patients
who were given six months to live,

80
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:02,640
yet lived for five, even ten years.

81
00:06:03,610 --> 00:06:04,640
Really?

82
00:06:05,575 --> 00:06:12,430
All those patients
wished strongly to keep living.

83
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:21,839
If Koharu can find her will to live
because of you,

84
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,760
then perhaps your actions have meaning.

85
00:06:42,665 --> 00:06:44,560
Koharu.

86
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,610
Yes?

87
00:06:51,515 --> 00:06:54,880
Kakeru, you're here today, too?

88
00:06:58,510 --> 00:06:59,510
Yeah.

89
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,410
Introducing my new beanie debut.

90
00:07:06,090 --> 00:07:07,600
It suits you.

91
00:07:08,705 --> 00:07:11,190
Maybe I'll buy the same one.

92
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:12,860
Matching outfits?

93
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,340
Um...

94
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:21,780
I got this for you.

95
00:07:29,540 --> 00:07:30,960
What is it?

96
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:33,320
Open it.

97
00:07:48,730 --> 00:07:49,830
A book?

98
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:53,740
Shuntaro Asama's new mystery novel.

99
00:07:54,925 --> 00:07:56,470
Huh?

100
00:07:56,470 --> 00:07:59,830
It's not out in braille
or as an audiobook yet.

101
00:08:04,490 --> 00:08:05,860
So...

102
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,610
Shall I read it for you?

103
00:08:13,745 --> 00:08:16,160
But if you read this...

104
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:18,450
It's about 700 pages.

105
00:08:19,820 --> 00:08:22,770
That would take a really long time.

106
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,410
That's fine.

107
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,430
Let's take our time.

108
00:08:41,310 --> 00:08:44,335
All right. Let's start.

109
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:46,630
Okay.

110
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:51,910
"<i>Braille's White Memory</i>."

111
00:08:57,276 --> 00:08:58,846
Delicious!

112
00:09:02,370 --> 00:09:04,980
What's with that gloomy face?

113
00:09:05,845 --> 00:09:08,750
I can't believe you can eat.

114
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:13,005
If we're all moping around,
it'll only make Koharu sad.

115
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:18,370
Do you like vinegar?

116
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:20,270
Yeah.

117
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:24,815
Well, I get how you feel.

118
00:09:24,815 --> 00:09:29,515
You're obviously worried for her,
and there's Kakeru too.

119
00:09:29,515 --> 00:09:30,515
Huh?

120
00:09:31,575 --> 00:09:34,300
He finally bounced back.

121
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:36,720
But if Koharu's gone again...

122
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:42,860
But, I think it'll be okay.

123
00:09:43,765 --> 00:09:44,980
What will?

124
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:46,615
Koharu.

125
00:09:46,615 --> 00:09:48,165
And of course, Kakeru.

126
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:53,070
They've already overcome so much hardship.

127
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,210
So...

128
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:58,790
They can overcome anything.

129
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,570
Let's trust them.

130
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:12,350
Chili oil.

131
00:10:13,265 --> 00:10:14,260
Hm?

132
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:15,850
Put a little more in.

133
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:20,970
Got it.

134
00:10:26,015 --> 00:10:28,680
If things get tough again, let's eat out.

135
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,555
I'm single anyway.

136
00:10:30,555 --> 00:10:32,155
Let's eat.

137
00:10:33,230 --> 00:10:35,120
All right, dig in!

138
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:43,360
So good!

139
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:47,525
Right? The gyoza here is amazing!

140
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:55,690
Koharu.

141
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,190
Koharu.

142
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,180
Huh?

143
00:11:16,615 --> 00:11:18,650
Koharu...

144
00:11:18,650 --> 00:11:20,090
Kakeru?

145
00:11:20,730 --> 00:11:22,830
What's wrong? You look pale.

146
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,250
What are you doing?

147
00:11:28,050 --> 00:11:29,560
Rehabilitation.

148
00:11:31,005 --> 00:11:35,130
I've been bedridden,
so I lost a lot of muscle.

149
00:11:37,165 --> 00:11:41,820
If I don't walk sometimes,
the illness will win.

150
00:11:43,430 --> 00:11:44,690
I see.

151
00:11:45,550 --> 00:11:49,730
On the day of the fireworks,
it'd be awful if I can't walk on my own.

152
00:12:00,615 --> 00:12:03,090
- I'll help you.
- Here you go.

153
00:12:07,445 --> 00:12:09,010
Let's walk.

154
00:12:09,010 --> 00:12:10,010
Okay.

155
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:15,410
That's it.

156
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:27,690
Here's a blanket.

157
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,790
There.

158
00:12:34,355 --> 00:12:35,840
Okay.

159
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:38,375
- Let's move.
- Okay.

160
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:48,670
Kakeru?

161
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:54,330
It's nothing.

162
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:57,410
Shall we go?

163
00:13:15,930 --> 00:13:17,970
Thank you, Yuuko.

164
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:22,940
Kakeru isn't very considerate
about these things, is he?

165
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:30,120
Is something wrong?

166
00:13:31,405 --> 00:13:32,730
Huh?

167
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:34,720
Your eyes are red.

168
00:13:39,755 --> 00:13:43,620
I'm terrible. I'm such a crybaby lately.

169
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:51,590
The truth is...

170
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:54,790
I might...

171
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:58,300
never be able to walk again.

172
00:14:00,510 --> 00:14:01,510
What?

173
00:14:02,490 --> 00:14:05,340
Apparently, the tumor in my brain
is spreading.

174
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:09,640
The paralysis in my legs
is getting worse, too.

175
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:14,930
So no matter how much rehab I do,
I probably can't...

176
00:14:20,770 --> 00:14:21,970
Sorry.

177
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:25,010
I'm kidding.

178
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:27,580
Ignore that.

179
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,450
I decided I'd fight
until the fireworks, and yet...

180
00:14:36,170 --> 00:14:37,210
Sorry.

181
00:14:49,635 --> 00:14:54,850
Koharu, do you remember when we first met?

182
00:14:57,370 --> 00:14:59,980
The college entrance ceremony.

183
00:15:00,705 --> 00:15:05,029
You were helping at the reception desk.

184
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:09,050
That day, you were wearing a dress, remember?

185
00:15:09,050 --> 00:15:11,785
I was so curious about it,

186
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:14,125
I asked, "Why are you wearing a dress?"

187
00:15:14,915 --> 00:15:16,210
Yeah.

188
00:15:16,210 --> 00:15:20,685
And then you said, "It's a special occasion."

189
00:15:20,685 --> 00:15:24,105
It'd be a waste
not to wear what you want."

190
00:15:25,370 --> 00:15:26,900
I remember.

191
00:15:27,540 --> 00:15:29,930
When I heard that...

192
00:15:32,130 --> 00:15:35,700
I thought you were really cool.

193
00:15:40,505 --> 00:15:45,417
You're so upfront about your feelings
and what you want to do.

194
00:15:45,417 --> 00:15:47,017
That's amazing.

195
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:53,150
I looked up to you,
and I wanted to be your friend.

196
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,260
So...

197
00:15:58,580 --> 00:16:01,420
because I love that about you, Koharu...

198
00:16:02,650 --> 00:16:05,780
I want you to always be honest
about how you feel.

199
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:12,380
Whether you're happy or suffering,

200
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:15,170
I want you to tell us.

201
00:16:27,210 --> 00:16:28,270
I'm sorry.

202
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,300
Thank you.

203
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:51,000
I don't want to die.

204
00:16:53,970 --> 00:16:54,980
Yeah.

205
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:00,330
I really don't want to die.

206
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:17,460
Can't sleep?

207
00:17:21,930 --> 00:17:23,900
Koharu's body...

208
00:17:26,090 --> 00:17:27,950
was so light.

209
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:32,020
When I was pushing the wheelchair.

210
00:17:35,170 --> 00:17:37,430
I didn't know she had gotten...

211
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:40,910
that much lighter.

212
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:46,020
She really might...

213
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,960
disappear like this.

214
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:53,450
That thought hit me.

215
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:30,440
Never thought I'd be comforted
by you in silence.

216
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,160
Obviously, I'd stay by your side.

217
00:18:39,630 --> 00:18:41,320
We're friends.

218
00:18:57,410 --> 00:18:59,370
We're just roommates.

219
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:06,300
Looks like you're back to normal.

220
00:19:11,195 --> 00:19:12,790
I'll start reading.

221
00:19:12,790 --> 00:19:14,190
Um...

222
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,410
Can I...

223
00:19:20,466 --> 00:19:23,076
ask for one selfish thing?

224
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:26,750
Yeah.

225
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:28,790
What is it?

226
00:19:30,070 --> 00:19:31,340
My hand...

227
00:19:32,836 --> 00:19:34,866
Can you hold it?

228
00:19:50,190 --> 00:19:53,760
Thank you...

229
00:19:57,260 --> 00:19:58,650
Koharu?

230
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:01,730
I'm okay.

231
00:20:02,690 --> 00:20:04,150
Stay like this...

232
00:20:06,310 --> 00:20:07,980
for a bit longer...

233
00:20:12,254 --> 00:20:14,949
<i>- Even after that,</i>
- Slowly.

234
00:20:14,949 --> 00:20:17,019
<i>Koharu continued her rehab.</i>

235
00:20:21,110 --> 00:20:23,780
<i>Her symptoms only continued to worsen.</i>

236
00:20:25,350 --> 00:20:27,518
<i>- But...</i>
- Should we stop for today?

237
00:20:27,518 --> 00:20:30,320
<i>she never gave up.</i>

238
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,960
I'll eat more.

239
00:20:33,045 --> 00:20:34,660
"It felt familiar."

240
00:20:34,660 --> 00:20:36,890
<i>Every day felt like a miracle.</i>

241
00:20:36,890 --> 00:20:39,515
"A hazy, distant day
that feels like a dream..."

242
00:20:39,515 --> 00:20:41,800
<i>Yesterday to today.</i>

243
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:43,350
<i>Today to tomorrow.</i>

244
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:49,940
<i>Koharu kept passing
the baton of life forward.</i>

245
00:20:55,420 --> 00:20:57,110
Happy New Year.

246
00:20:58,725 --> 00:21:00,370
Happy New Year.

247
00:21:00,370 --> 00:21:05,190
<i>The new year began,
and the day of the fireworks arrived.</i>

248
00:21:07,527 --> 00:21:11,270
<i>Koharu was still alive.</i>

249
00:21:18,946 --> 00:21:22,856
Ushio says he got us premium seats.

250
00:21:25,230 --> 00:21:28,420
He really went
first thing in the morning, huh?

251
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,960
He left at 3 a.m.

252
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:36,380
I can't wait.

253
00:21:40,367 --> 00:21:42,877
After the fireworks are over...

254
00:21:44,317 --> 00:21:46,057
what should we do next?

255
00:21:48,755 --> 00:21:51,420
You're getting ahead of yourself.

256
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:53,100
Not at all.

257
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:56,720
You're...

258
00:21:59,096 --> 00:22:01,086
going to keep living.

259
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:06,690
Let's plan even more fun things to do.

260
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:09,500
Today...

261
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:12,440
tomorrow, the day after,

262
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:15,450
and from now on...

263
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:21,300
Yeah.

264
00:22:24,726 --> 00:22:26,056
Then...

265
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:29,230
let's go...

266
00:22:31,130 --> 00:22:32,630
to the sea.

267
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,260
The sea sounds nice.

268
00:22:40,170 --> 00:22:41,940
The sound of the waves.

269
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,030
The feeling of the sand.

270
00:22:50,230 --> 00:22:51,330
But...

271
00:22:52,450 --> 00:22:54,590
isn't it still cold?

272
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:59,620
Then we'll go in the summer.

273
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,710
In the spring,

274
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:06,430
how about a trip?

275
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:11,380
That sounds nice.

276
00:23:13,505 --> 00:23:15,480
A hot spring.

277
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:18,125
Surrounded by mountains,

278
00:23:18,125 --> 00:23:20,335
under a starry sky at night.

279
00:23:21,690 --> 00:23:23,230
And then...

280
00:23:27,550 --> 00:23:28,930
Koharu?

281
00:23:32,090 --> 00:23:33,360
Koharu.

282
00:23:34,375 --> 00:23:35,766
Koharu.

283
00:23:35,766 --> 00:23:37,056
Koharu!

284
00:23:39,630 --> 00:23:42,250
Koharu! Koharu!

285
00:23:45,535 --> 00:23:47,760
I wish I could live in a way

286
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:51,470
that leaves a mark on someone's heart,
like fireworks do.

287
00:23:51,470 --> 00:23:53,490
I'm so glad I met you, Koharu.

288
00:23:53,490 --> 00:23:55,894
Everything is done now.

289
00:23:55,894 --> 00:23:59,479
Kakeru, I will always love you.
